      </div>
      <p style="font-size:12px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--ink-3)">
        Each modifier scales the probability directly by its odds ratio. <strong>Advantage:</strong> simple, transparent, produces an output identical to back-of-envelope clinical reasoning ("this patient is in the high-risk group, probably around 60–80%"). <strong>Assumption:</strong> modifiers act independently on probability. <strong>Failure mode:</strong> at the extremes, compounding protective modifiers can produce implausibly low probabilities (e.g. male + high BMI + older age + pencil-point all combining).
      </p>

      <!-- Method B -->
