      <div class="meth-sub">How the pooled treatment effect becomes the "one headache prevented per N patients" number on the Clinical Summary tab.</div>
      <div class="meth-eq">
        <code>1. baseline risk p<sub>0</sub> = P(PDPH | ADP, patient)   // from §1</code><br>
        <code>2. baseline odds  o<sub>0</sub> = p<sub>0</sub> / (1 − p<sub>0</sub>)</code><br>
        <code>3. treated odds   o<sub>1</sub> = o<sub>0</sub> × OR</code><br>
        <code>4. treated risk   p<sub>1</sub> = o<sub>1</sub> / (1 + o<sub>1</sub>)</code><br>
        <code>5. ARR            = p<sub>0</sub> − p<sub>1</sub></code><br>
        <code>6. NNT            = round(1 / ARR)</code>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.55;margin-top:.5rem"><strong>Worked example</strong> — obstetric 17G Tuohy ADP, baseline probability 72%, administered &lt;24h post-ADP (pooled OR 0.20):</p>
      <div class="meth-worked">
